n-debt-bankrtupcy-biden-reforms-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20guidance%20it%20released%20in%202022%3C%2Fa%3E.%20According%20to%20the%20department%2C%20588%20new%20cases%20were%20filed%20from%20October%202023%20to%20March%202024%2C%20marking%20a%2036%25%20increase%20from%20the%20prior%206-month%20period.%20Most%20of%20those%20borrowers%20have%20also%20seen%20success%20in%20court%20%E2%80%94%20per%20the%20department%2C%2098%25%20of%20them%20received%20full%20or%20partial%20debt%20relief%20from%20November%202022%20through%20March%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrior%20to%20the%20guidance%2C%20borrowers%20had%20to%20prove%20an%20%26quot%3Bundue%20hardship%26quot%3B%20standard%2C%20in%20which%20they%20had%20to%20show%20that%20they%20could%20not%20maintain%20a%20minimal%20standard%20of%20living%2C%20that%20their%20circumstances%20weren't%20likely%20to%20improve%2C%20and%20that%20they%20had%20made%20a%20good-faith%20effort%20to%20repay%20their%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20that%20standard%20was%20very%20challenging%20for%20borrowers%20to%20meet%2C%20so%20the%20Education%20and%20Justice%20Departments%20streamlined%20the%20process%20by%20establishing%20clearer%20guidelines%20for%20borrowers%20to%20prove%20undue%20hardship.%20Those%20included%20examining%20whether%20borrowers%20have%20made%20a%20good%20faith%20effort%20to%20repay%20their%20debt%20and%20determining%20their%20future%20ability%20to%20make%20payments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20guidance%20also%20allowed%20borrowers%20to%20complete%20a%20self-attestation%20form%2C%20which%20allowed%20departments%20to%20process%20their%20discharge%20requests%20faster%20and%20avoid%20investigations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20clear%2C%20fair%2C%20and%20practical%20standards%20are%20helping%20struggling%20borrowers%20find%20relief%20that%20was%20previously%20out%20of%20reach%2C%26quot%3B%20Under%20Secretary%20of%20Education%20James%20Kvaal%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20data%20shoul